cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with anomaly detection in images using a convolutional autoencoder and a distance-based anomaly detector. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of an Inception-like architecture for the autoencoder suggests a focus on deep learning (cs.NE) and the use of product quantization for approximate distance computation suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach for anomaly detection, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories.
